basicStepDescription: Configure the common information for your connector instance.
configurationStepDescription: Configure the connector-specific information for your connector instance.
connectKafkaWithSA: Connect to the Kafka instance using this client ID and secret
connectorTypeStepDescription: The selected connector is the basis for your Connectors instance. There are two types of connectors: source and sink. A source connector ingests data from another system into a Kafka instance. A sink connector propagates data from a Kafka instance into another system.
creationSuccessAlertDescription: {{name}} Connectors instance is ready for use.
errorHandlingStepDescription: Configure error handling stop, log and dead letter queues
evalNamespaceExpire: The eval connectors instance and its namespace will expire in
genericErrorBody: There was a problem processing the request. Please try again.
gettingStartedBody: To get started, create a Connector. For help getting started, access <2>getting-started-connectors</2>
kafkaStepDescription: The selected Kafka instance works with your Connectors instance. A source connector ingests data from another system into a Kafka instance. A sink connector propagates data from a Kafka instance into another system.
leaveCreateConnectorConfirmModalDescript: Changes you have made will be lost and no connector will be created.
leaveDuplicateConnectorConfirmModalDescr: Changes you have made will be lost and no connector will be created.
leaveEditConfirmModalDescription: Changes you have made to the connector properties will not be saved.
name: Name
namespaceEmptyMsg: You can deploy connector instance on your own OSD cluster or register an eval namespace provided by Red Hat owned OSD for evaluation purpose.
namespaceExpireAlert: The eval namespace has a duration of 48 hours. The Connector hosted on this namespace will expire when the namespace are not available.
namespaceModelAlert: The namespace will be ready shortly after registration.
namespaceStepDescription: The selected namespace hosts your Connectors instance. Use a namespace in an OpenShift Dedicated trial cluster, or have Red Hat create a preview namespace for you. For instructions on adding a namespace to a trial cluster, access the guide.
noFilterResultsFound: No results match the filter criteria. <2>{t('clearAllFilters')}</2> to show results.
noKafkaInstanceAvailableBody: To select a Kafka instance for your Connectors instance to work with, create a new one.
reviewJSONStepDescription:
Review the configuration properties for your connector instance.
The JSON shown only includes the properties needed to configure the connector instance. Properties where default values are used are not included in the JSON.
reviewStepDescription: Review the configuration properties for your connector instance.
serviceAccountAlertMsg: Make a copy of the client ID and secret to store in a safe place. The client secret won't appear again after closing this screen.
serviceAccountDescText: A service account enables the Connectors instance to authenticate with the Kafka instance. Provide credentials of an existing service account that has access to the Kafka instance or create a new service account.
shortDescriptionExampleText: Must start with a letter and end with a letter or number. Valid characters include lowercase letters from a to z, numbers from 0 to 9, and hyphens ( - ).
shortDescriptionHelpText: The short description is the same as the client name in the underlying OAuth system.
